President Trump held a meeting in the Roosevelt Room to discuss the issue of surprise medical bills and the need for transparency in healthcare pricing. He emphasized the importance of delivering a healthcare system that provides affordable and high-quality care for the American people. The President highlighted the progress made in lowering healthcare costs, including the approval of a record number of generic drugs and the expansion of association health plans. He also mentioned the decline in prescription drug prices in 2018 for the first time in over 50 years. Secretary Acosta provided an update on the success of association health plans, which have resulted in cost savings and improved quality of healthcare. Secretary Azar discussed the need for transparency in healthcare pricing and the efforts made to bring down costs for patients. The President also addressed other topics such as Venezuela, the State of the Union address, and the ongoing negotiations with China.